      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KEAYANG ALABAMA (2) was well supported and made a solid impact on debut a week-and-a-half ago over 1690m at Kilmore, beaten 4 metres into second after taking charge of proceedings a fair way from home. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Meets a similar line up so he is capable of getting the job done. MAJOR ROY (1) was responsible for a very good effort last time over 2100m at Charlton, finishing third and just 2 metres from the winner. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Meets a comparable field and he can take this out. COLOSIMO (3) produced a good effort on debut last start, finishing third over 2180m at Terang. Has plenty of scope for improvement. STEEL MIKI (6) could only finish eighth over 1690m at Kilmore most recently. Open to improvement and is in the mix.",
